      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 11 obituary of Ronald L Ridenhour</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an obituary on May 11 about Ronald L. Ridenhour, the Vietnam veteran who in 1969 disclosed the My Lai massacre of civilians by United States troops, misstated the title held at the time by Morris K. Udall. He was Mr. Ridenhour's Representative, not a Senator.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
